              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>the form or nature of something, with special reference to its outer form or structure</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>form</Gloss>
                <Gloss>nature</Gloss>
                <Gloss>structure</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In {S:04600703100024} σχῆμα does not refer to the physical form of the earth but to the way of life in the world. The reference is primarily to culture rather than to physical form. It is possible, therefore, to render this expression in {S:04600703100024} as ‘the way of life in this world is passing away.’</Comments>
